For high-altitude:

1 cup blue cornmeal
1 cup all-purpose flour
¾ tsp baking soda
1 ½ tsp baking powder
¾ tsp kosher salt
¾ cup buttermilk
¼ cup light brown sugar
2 large eggs
1 cup ripe blueberries
1 tbsp white sugar
5 tbsp unsalted butter

Toss blueberries in sugar, allow to rest. 
Preheat oven to 425F.
Melt butter, allow to cool
Whisk cornmeal, flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl.
In a large bowl mix buttermilk, eggs and brown sugar. Add melted butter.
Add dry mix, stir until just combined (should still be *small* swirls of dry mix remaining)
Fold in blueberries.

Pour batter into an 8 inch square baking pan and cook for 15-18 mins until brown and crispy on top and toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Cool for about 10 mins before serving.